This paper deals with learning probabilistic models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Bayesian networks also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of clustering algorithms suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
